<Layout title="Words With All Vowels — Vowel-Only Scrabble Words | ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" description="Find valid Scrabble words made entirely (or almost entirely) of vowels. Essential knowledge for vowel-heavy racks — AA, AI, OE, EAU and more." keywords="all vowel words scrabble, vowel only words, words made of vowels, aa scrabble word, eau scrabble, vowel dump words scrabble">

<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Words With All Vowels — Vowel-Only Scrabble Words",
  "datePublished": "2026-06-15",
  "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/" },
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/" }
})} />

<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What Scrabble words are made only of vowels?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Valid vowel-only words include AA (2 pts), AI (2 pts), OE (2 pts), and EAU (3 pts). In SOWPODS, additional options like EUOUAE (6 pts) — a medieval musical term — provide longer vowel-only plays." }},
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is AA a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes! AA is valid in both SOWPODS and TWL. It refers to a type of rough lava. Despite scoring only 2 points, AA is essential for parallel plays and tight board positions when your rack is vowel-heavy." }},
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the longest vowel-only Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "EUOUAE (6 letters) is considered the longest vowel-only word valid in SOWPODS. It's a medieval musical mnemonic. In TWL, EAU (3 letters) is the longest commonly accepted vowel-only word." }}
  ]
})} />

<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
<article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">

<nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
