<BlogCrossLinks current={slug} />

<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Words With All Vowels — Vowel-Only Scrabble Words</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 4 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">When your rack looks like a bowl of alphabet soup — all vowels, no consonants — you need words made entirely of vowel tiles. These rare but valid words let you play without exchanging, keeping your turn while dumping excess vowels. Every competitive player memorises these.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Complete Vowel-Only Words</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AA</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">2 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">2 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">2 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">2 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OI</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">2 pts</span></span>
  <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">EAU</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">3 pts</span></span>
</div>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Dictionary Note</p>
  <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Some vowel-only words are <span class="text-white font-medium">SOWPODS-only</span> (AE, OE, OI). Always verify which dictionary your game uses before playing these. AA, AI, and EAU are valid in both TWL and SOWPODS.</p>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">High-Vowel Words (1 Consonant Max)</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
  <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
    <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
      <tr>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Word</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Points</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Vowels</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Notes</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100 dark:divide-gray-800">
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">ADIEU</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3">4 of 5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Only D is consonant</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">AUDIO</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3">4 of 5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Only D is consonant</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">OURIE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">4 of 5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Only R is consonant</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">URAEI</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">4 of 5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Only R is consonant</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">LOOIE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">4 of 5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Only L is consonant</td></tr>
      <tr class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono font-bold">OORIE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-600 font-bold">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">4 of 5</td><td class="px-4 py-3">Only R is consonant (SOWPODS)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy for Vowel-Heavy Racks</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play before exchanging:</span> Even AA for 2 points is better than losing your turn to exchange. You dump a vowel, keep your turn, and draw a fresh tile that's likely a consonant.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Stack parallel plays:</span> AA parallel to an existing word creates two plays in one — the 2-letter word vertically PLUS whatever you form horizontally. This multiplies your meagre vowel score.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Premium squares save vowel plays:</span> AA on a double-word square = 4 points. EAU through a triple-letter = 5 points. Always look for premium square access before settling for a basic vowel dump.</p>
  </div>
</div>

